{"title":"New Tatze LINK 8.8mm thin pedal promises more ground clearance and mega grip","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/30/new-tatze-link-8-8mm-thin-pedal-promises-more-ground-clearance-and-mega-grip/","date":1630330178000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div data-off-canvas-content=\"\"><main role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-269768\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><header></header><section itemprop=\"text\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30081536/tatze-link-thin-mtb-flat-pedal.jpg\"><figure><img width=\"1400\" height=\"933\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30081536/tatze-link-thin-mtb-flat-pedal.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs%3Adevice%2Frscb28-1\" alt=\"tatze link flat pedal mtb thin 8.8mm outside edge\" loading=\"eager\" data-feature=\"1\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\"></figure></a><p>Tatze Bike Components have a new super thin flat pedal for mountain biking, the TATZE LINK. At just 8.8mm thick at the outside edge, the LINK pedal is due to be one of the thinnest MTB pedals ever to have made it to market. It’s svelte profile makes it pretty lightweight, too, weighing a claimed 343g for the standard version, and an ultralight 298g for the titanium axle version. Here’s what we know so far.</p><h2>Tatze LINK MTB Pedal</h2><p>This is not the thinnest flat pedal we’ve seen from Tatze. A few years ago at Eurobike, they showed the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/05/11/found-tatze-blade-flat-pedals-are-just-3mm-thick-w-bearing-housed-in-custom-crank-arm/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Tatze Blade</a> which had an incredibly thin outside edge of just 3mm. That was only possible using a design wherein the pedal bearing was integrated into a custom crank arm, the so-called Tatze Integral Standard. For reasons we may only hypothesize on, the Blade never actually made it to market. It may be because you couldn’t run them on a standard crank, a reason why FlyPaper pedals never quite made it.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins.jpg\" alt=\"tatze link 8.8mm thin flat pedal mtb\" width=\"1400\" height=\"817\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins-297x173.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins-800x467.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins-120x70.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins-768x448.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins-297x173.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins-800x467.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins-120x70.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091038/tatze-link-ultra-thin-flat-mtb-pedal-10-pins-768x448.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>Moving on, Tatze will be bringing an 8.8mm thick pedal to market in March 2022; the Tatze LINK. This one doesn’t require a custom crank, with all the usual internals housed inside the pedal body itself. That includes the axle (steel or titanium), two inboard bearings, an IGUS JSM bushing and a double seal on the outboard side. This central area is of course thicker than 8.8mm, but the 10 traction pins that thread into the pedal body stand clear of the relatively enlarged central portion that houses the internals.</p><div id=\"attachment_269791\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-269791\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge.jpg\" alt=\"tatze link flat pedal mtb 99mm x 113mm ultra thin concave platform 10 pins optional additional 4\" width=\"1400\" height=\"700\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge-297x149.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge-800x400.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge-120x60.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge-297x149.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge-800x400.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge-120x60.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091035/tatze-link-flat-pedals-mtb-very-thing-edge-768x384.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-269791\">The open design of the platform is said to be good for mud clearance, allowing it to fall through the holes</p></div><p>The pedal body itself is made up of 6061-T6 aluminium. The platform is said to be slightly concave, measuring 99mm across and 113mm from front to back. While the outside edge is just 8.8mm thick, the edges at the front and rear of the pedal are slightly thinker at 9.9mm. The Tatze LINK will ship with 10 pins installed in each side, but there are an additional 4 holes for riders who feel the need to run up to 14 pins on each side. The pins themselves are 6mm tall and 3.6mm in diameter.</p><div id=\"attachment_269793\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-269793\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile.jpg\" alt=\"tatze link ultra thin flat mtb pedals 8.8mm thick outside edge low profile more clearance emtbs\" width=\"1400\" height=\"467\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile-297x99.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile-800x267.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile-120x40.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile-768x256.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile-297x99.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile-800x267.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile-120x40.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30091312/tatze-link-ultra-thin-mtb-pedal-profile-768x256.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-269793\">The pins positioned in the central region are lower in height than those at the edge, helping to create a concave contact point with the shoe</p></div><p>The new pedal, deigned and tested in Tyrol, Austria, is said to be designed for “performance-oriented enduro and downhill riders”. As one of the thinnest pedals on the market, the Tatze LINK may be an attractive option for bikes with a very low bottom bracket, like many eMTBs that tend to rely on running shorter 165mm crank arms for additional ground clearance.</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>The Tatze LINK will be available with a steel axle and a titanium axle, priced at €145 and €229, respectively, each supplied with 40 spare pins. Replacement bushings, bearings and seals will be available too. Tatze say the pedal can be serviced up to 5 times.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://tatze-bike.com/en/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Tatze-Bike.com</em></a></p></section></article></main></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3f1230f3368291d1a6cbfaa4189ed6363cab105d70e37f76a1be8debc97949a9","category":"Cycling"}